    <div class="content-page" dir="ltr">
    <h1>Real-Time Strategy (RTS): Think Fast, Act Faster</h1>
    
    <p>Welcome to the fast-paced, adrenaline-fueled world of Real-Time Strategy. Unlike board games where you wait for your turn, in an RTS, everything happens all at once. You, your allies, and your enemies are constantly gathering resources, building bases, and commanding armies simultaneously. There are no pauses, and every second counts.</p>
    
    <h3>The Art of War Economy</h3>
    <p>A crucial part of any RTS is resource management. You can't build an army without the economy to support it! Balancing how many workers are mining gold or chopping wood versus how many soldiers are on the front lines is what separates the beginners from the grandmasters. A strong economy will inevitably overwhelm a smaller opponent.</p>

    <h3>Is this genre for you?</h3>
    <p>If you love multitasking, quick decision-making under pressure, and the thrill of out-managing your opponent in real-time, RTS is your home. It requires high actions-per-minute (APM) and rewards players who can keep an eye on the big picture while micromanaging individual battles.</p>
    
    <h3>Must-Play Masterpieces</h3>
    
    <h4>1. StarCraft II</h4>
    <p>Set in a distant sci-fi future, <em>StarCraft II</em> is the undisputed king of modern esports RTS. You choose between three completely unique factions (Terran, Zerg, or Protoss) and battle for galactic dominance. It's incredibly fast, competitive, and has a thrilling cinematic story campaign.</p>
    
    <img src="images/starcraft battle.jpg" alt="StarCraft II base and battle" class="page-image" />
    
    <h4>2. Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition</h4>
    <p>If sci-fi isn't your style, how about rewriting human history? <em>Age of Empires II</em> lets you guide a historical civilization from the Dark Ages to the Imperial Age. You'll build massive stone castles, farm for food, and command armies of knights and archers in epic medieval warfare.</p>
    
    <img src="images/castle aoe2.jpg" alt="Age of Empires II massive castle siege" class="page-image" />

    <h4>3. Warcraft III: Reign of Chaos</h4>
    <p>This game completely revolutionized the genre by blending RTS with RPG elements. In <em>Warcraft III</em>, you don't just build armies; you also command powerful "Heroes" who level up, equip magical items, and use devastating spells. Fun fact: The custom map editor in this game is what gave birth to the entire MOBA genre!</p>
    
    <img src="images/warcraft3.jpeg" alt="Warcraft III hero unit in battle" class="page-image" />

    <h4>4. Command & Conquer: Red Alert Series</h4>
    <p>Welcome to an alternate history where time travel altered the course of World War II, leading to an epic showdown between the Allies and the Soviet Union. <em>Red Alert</em> is famous for its fast-paced tank rushes, iconic superweapons like the Chronosphere and Tesla Coils, and its incredibly cheesy but lovable live-action cutscenes.</p>
    
    <img src="images/redalert.jpg" alt="Red Alert massive tank battle" class="page-image" />
    
    <h3>Dive Deeper</h3>
    <p>Want to learn more about where these games came from and how the genre evolved over the decades? <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real-time_strategy#History" target="_blank">Check out this comprehensive history of Real-Time Strategy games</a>.</p>
